LevelDBUWP is a port of LevelDB (originally made by Google) for Universal Windows Platform (UWP).
summary: LevelDBUWP is a port of LevelDB (originally made by Google) for Universal Windows Platform (UWP). LevelDB stores keys and values in arbitrary byte arrays, and data is sorted by key. It supports batching writes, forward and backward iteration, and compression of the data via Google's Snappy compression library.

summary: LevelDBUWP is a port of LevelDB (originally made by Google) for Universal Windows Platform (UWP). LevelDB stores keys and values in arbitrary byte arrays, and data is sorted by key. It supports batching writes, forward and backward iteration, and compression of the data via Google's Snappy compression library.
